result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley A. Durst was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Conditions:

No possession or consumption of alcohol.  No possession or consumption of any controlled substances and/or prescription drugs for which the Defendant does not have a valid prescription.

Cooperate with (attend, pay for, and successfully complete) any treatment or assessment program deemed necessary by the supervising agency.

Submit to AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations of the counselor.

Submit DNA sample.

Pay court costs and costs of supervision.

90 days conditional jail time, with huber, and to be served in any Wisconsin county jail that will accept.  This conditional time to be stayed for up to 30 days, until on or before July 3, 2016.  Also, imposed and stayed are an additional 120 days in jail that P/P can request be imposed.  

No credit in the event of revocation.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Defendant Ashley A. Durst in court with attorney Lisa A McDougal. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin. PSI has been received and reviewed by counsel and Court. Atty. M states clarifications. Counsel each make their arguments for sentencing. Agent MCJ addresses the Court. Sentence withheld for 3 years probation with no drink/no possess condition; also, not to possess/consume any prescriptions/controlled substances for which def does not have a prescription; cooperate with any treatment or assessment program deemed necessary by the agency; AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations of the counselor; submit DNA sample; pay court-ordered financial obligations.  Further condition:  90 days conditional jail time imposed, with huber, and stayed for 30 days.  Also, imposed and stayed are an additional 120 days in the Richland County Jail that the P/P can request be imposed; if P/P makes such request, it would be done via filing of the agent, with stipulation of the defendant.
Sentencing hearing on June 3, 2016 at 09:00 am.
